=Bio=

"I am completing a PhD at The University of Melbourne, investigating the political dynamic of Open Projects (projects influenced by the principles and production models of Free and Open Source Software, but translated into different domains). For the last two years I have also been working on the CPOV Wikipedia project, which aims to foster critical perspectives in Wikipedia research. Beginning 2011, I will be working on a project called Mundane Platforms, which explores questions of software and agency, global development, media ontology and method, and the everyday."


=Research=

"My research interests include:

FLOSS, Software and Platform Studies, Philosophy of Technology, Cybernetics, Political Theory, ANT, STS, Development Studies and Network Cultures"


